1
00:00:00,830 --> 00:00:07,589
Market manipulation occurs on a daily basis,
right under the noses of retail traders.

2
00:00:07,589 --> 00:00:10,540
You witness this yourself, every day.

3
00:00:10,540 --> 00:00:17,350
And you’re wondering why the theory of support
and resistance you read in almost every trading

4
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:20,270
book, doesn’t seem to work in real markets.

5
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:27,019
Today I’m sharing my experience with support
and resistance trading, but in the context

6
00:00:27,019 --> 00:00:33,210
of smart money, and you’ll learn the best
practices to trade, and avoid being manipulated

7
00:00:33,210 --> 00:00:35,590
by big market players.

8
00:00:35,590 --> 00:00:41,149
You know the drill, like, subscribe, and stick
around for the full video.

9
00:00:41,149 --> 00:00:48,740
The biggest lie in trading
True or false?

10
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:53,420
The more times a level is tested, the more
“valid” it is.

11
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:56,230
If you said true, you are wrong!

12
00:00:56,230 --> 00:00:59,940
This statement is one of the biggest lies
in trading.

13
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:07,970
In my experience, really strong support/resistance
levels immediately push price away from them.

14
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:14,159
There is enough buying pressure at support
(enough buyers waiting to buy at the level),

15
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:19,240
that the market is immediately moved up and
away from the level.

16
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:25,590
If price can hang around the level or quickly
comes back to the level, it suggests a certain

17
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:30,280
lack of conviction on the part of the bulls.

18
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:36,690
If the market is able to retest the level
many times, then you have a potential setup

19
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:40,030
for a breakout through the level.

20
00:01:40,030 --> 00:01:49,649
In this example, the orders at the support
level are absorbed each time price revisits

21
00:01:49,649 --> 00:01:54,450
the area, until buyers lose their power.

22
00:01:54,450 --> 00:01:58,530
Price then plunges through the zone with little
difficulty.

23
00:01:58,530 --> 00:02:03,079
And also look at this resistance level.

24
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:09,440
The upper zone was tested several times and
sellers came in pushing the price down.

25
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:17,840
This resistance level was gradually eroded
as more and more sellers had their order filled.

26
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:23,650
Eventually there were less sellers and price
broke through.

27
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:32,410
Personally, I avoid buying a support which
has been tested multiple times in the past.

28
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:39,050
The greater the number of times a zone is
tested, the more likely it is to break.

29
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:45,160
When a support area is tested multiple times,
some or all of the waiting buy orders are

30
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:50,890
executed, leaving less willing buyers at that
level.

31
00:02:50,890 --> 00:02:58,909
Once all the buyers have gone, price can move
through that level to the next area.

32
00:02:58,909 --> 00:03:04,940
From my experience, the best entry is the
one where price drops to support and quickly

33
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:10,739
moves up, leaving a long shadow on the candle
that dropped through support.

34
00:03:10,739 --> 00:03:13,290
A liquidity clear-out.

35
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:20,920
I would much rather buy a broken support,
after a liquidity clear-out, than clean support…

36
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:27,000
that trade is 10 times better (to me) than
buying a clean, exact support level.

37
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:37,270
Strong imbalance between buyers and sellers
At one point, price leaves a support or resistance

38
00:03:37,270 --> 00:03:39,800
level and starts trending.

39
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:47,750
A strong imbalance between buyers and sellers
leads to strong and explosive price movements.

40
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:54,420
As a rule of thumb, remember that the stronger
the movement away from a level, the more interest

41
00:03:54,420 --> 00:04:00,409
will usually still exist – especially when
the time spent at the level was relatively

42
00:04:00,409 --> 00:04:01,409
short.

43
00:04:01,409 --> 00:04:08,940
So when price goes from selling off to a strong
bullish trend, there had to be a significant

44
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:15,800
amount of buy interest entering the market,
absorbing all sell orders AND then driving

45
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:19,769
price higher.

46
00:04:19,769 --> 00:04:27,710
So the next time price revisits the area,
I would be very interested to buy that support.

47
00:04:27,710 --> 00:04:35,040
Always look for extremely strong turning points;
these are often high probability price levels.

48
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:46,560
Price manipulation around support and resistance
Price manipulation is a series of actions

49
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:54,440
carried out by smart money to induce either
buying or selling activity from other traders.

50
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,810
Why would they do that?

51
00:04:56,810 --> 00:05:02,810
Smart money uses position sizes that stop
them from simply hitting buy or sell as you

52
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:05,460
and I would do.

53
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:11,410
Because their position sizes are so massive
they must enter over a period of time so as

54
00:05:11,410 --> 00:05:17,120
to not spike the price and reveal the position
they’re entering.

55
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:23,960
Because of this they have to seek out areas
in the market where there is enough liquidity.

56
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:30,850
A great deal of orders reside around support
and resistance zones.

57
00:05:30,850 --> 00:05:45,150
Stop Entering When the Pro's are Taking Profit
Take a look at this example.

58
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:51,270
This shows a very common pattern in the market:
the key differences of where the professional

59
00:05:51,270 --> 00:05:56,560
money enters and where the retail trader enters.

60
00:05:56,560 --> 00:06:03,370
The retail trader buys and takes a long trade
when price breaks a previous resistance level

61
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:06,680
and price is at a new high.

62
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:10,509
Admit it, it’s a strategy you use often.

63
00:06:10,509 --> 00:06:15,319
But soon after the entry, price moves lower
from the previous high.

64
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:18,060
And you often times get stopped out.

65
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:25,540
At the same time you are stopped out, the
professional traders are entering the market.

66
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:31,280
That’s the difference between retail and
smart money.

67
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:34,930
Retail traders buy at support.

68
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:38,940
Smart money buy below support.

69
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:44,850
And when price moves higher the professional
traders will cover their long trades and start

70
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:47,370
taking their profit.

71
00:06:47,370 --> 00:06:53,960
At that time, the retail traders are just
starting to enter long.

72
00:06:53,960 --> 00:07:00,381
When you enter from these areas that are at
extreme highs or lows, the big guys are taking

73
00:07:00,381 --> 00:07:02,180
profit.

74
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:07,330
And obviously entering the market when the
smart money are getting out is not a smart

75
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:08,330
plan.

76
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:16,350
A common saying in trading is: buy any weakness
and sell any strength.

77
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:23,980
So if price moves lower from an extreme high
then you can look to buy from a value area,

78
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:35,280
and if price moves higher from an extreme
low, price can be sold from a value area.

79
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:42,430
Here’s price moving from an extreme high
back lower.

80
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:51,090
This is price showing weakness and moving
to a value area for a possible buy entry.

81
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:57,750
If you have entered a long trade from the
high, you would have been stopped out.

82
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:03,430
But if you have instead entered a long trade
when price showed weakness and moved back

83
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:08,710
lower, you would have entered at a much better
area.

84
00:08:08,710 --> 00:08:18,129
The consolidation trap
Price spends most of its time in consolidation.

85
00:08:18,129 --> 00:08:21,850
This is the market showing you a balance in
price.

86
00:08:21,850 --> 00:08:24,870
There are several reasons for the price to
consolidate.

87
00:08:24,870 --> 00:08:29,509
One of them is liquidity generation.

88
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:35,690
When price consolidates for an extended period
of time, the masses start to place support

89
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:42,219
and resistance levels at the extremes of the
consolidation zone.

90
00:08:42,219 --> 00:08:50,910
Any sudden break out of this consolidation
range will tempt traders to enter.

91
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:57,360
These entry opportunities are traps set by
the market makers using this consolidation

92
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:00,829
technique.

93
00:09:00,829 --> 00:09:05,760
If you’re using certain indicators, things
are even worse.

94
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:11,870
When the market is in consolidation, moving
averages, probably the most common indicator,

95
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:14,370
will get very close together.

96
00:09:14,370 --> 00:09:21,620
The most common entry signal is given to retail
traders when these 2 moving averages cross.

97
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:28,790
A breakout outside the consolidation, plus
the crossover, indicate to retail traders

98
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:33,709
that the trend has now changed.

99
00:09:33,709 --> 00:09:36,519
This is “a false” signal that the price
will increase.

100
00:09:36,519 --> 00:09:44,280
All of these confirmations are seducing the
average retail trader to take a buy position,

101
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:50,210
in order for the smart money to fill their
massive sell positions.

102
00:09:50,210 --> 00:09:56,300
And by the time the indicators signal the
change to a downtrend the market has already

103
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:59,529
made most of its move.

104
00:09:59,529 --> 00:10:06,060
The point is: smart money knows that even
the smallest break outside of a consolidation

105
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:10,380
area will set off the signal to the masses.

106
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:17,529
This is well known tactic used by market makers
to trick retail traders into buying or selling

107
00:10:17,529 --> 00:10:28,029
certain levels.

108
00:10:28,029 --> 00:10:29,029
Liquidity clear-outs

109
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:32,149
Liquidity is just a fancy word for you taking
a position.

110
00:10:32,149 --> 00:10:37,160
The more people taking positions, the more
liquidity you have.

111
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:43,920
The big players need LOTS of liquidity in
order to fill their massive orders.

112
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:46,630
How do you think they get this liquidity?

113
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:52,959
By creating well known retail chart patterns,
in order to involve the retail traders into

114
00:10:52,959 --> 00:10:55,620
the market.

115
00:10:55,620 --> 00:11:01,089
These patterns are used by smart money to
induce you take a position.

116
00:11:01,089 --> 00:11:06,720
You might have a small account, and trade
with mini lots, but remember, millions of

117
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:12,100
beginner traders are in your shoes, and use
the same information to trade.

118
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:18,410
Smart money vs dumb money

119
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:22,790
Trading will always be a game against the
smart money and the dumb money.

120
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:28,910
How many times have you traded a triangle
pattern, for example, just for the price to

121
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:35,029
do the exact opposite as soon as you jump
into your position?

122
00:11:35,029 --> 00:11:41,130
Retail traders might see these patterns as
continuation patterns, but the smart money

123
00:11:41,130 --> 00:11:47,240
are seeing them as reversal patterns.

124
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:52,279
You have to start putting yourself in the
shoes of the large institutions and big-money

125
00:11:52,279 --> 00:11:53,779
players.

126
00:11:53,779 --> 00:11:57,110
Think like the hunter, not the prey.

127
00:11:57,110 --> 00:12:02,660
Always remember that smart money are always
searching for pockets of liquidity in order

128
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:06,050
to fill their desired positions in the market.

129
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:13,149
They are always looking to shake out weak
hands, particularly around support and resistance

130
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:16,779
levels that are being widely watched.

131
00:12:16,779 --> 00:12:23,970
It’s time to reconsider how you see support
and resistance levels and to start building

132
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:29,880
a strategy that allows you to join the smart
money, after a liquidity clear-out.

133
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:39,079
Trade In The Direction Of The Most Recent
valid High/Low

134
00:12:39,079 --> 00:12:44,180
Most of the traders who trade support and
resistance try to predict where a movement

135
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:50,290
will end instead of trading in the direction
of the movement itself.

136
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:56,839
What these traders typically tend to do is
mark all the levels which the market hasn’t

137
00:12:56,839 --> 00:13:03,269
encountered yet and wait for the price to
enter these zones before going either long

138
00:13:03,269 --> 00:13:04,269
or short.

139
00:13:04,269 --> 00:13:10,959
But there are lots of levels forming in the
direction of the current movement which the

140
00:13:10,959 --> 00:13:18,269
trader is neglecting to trade because he is
so focused on predicting where the price will

141
00:13:18,269 --> 00:13:19,620
reverse.

142
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:26,029
My advice is to start taking trades at levels
which formed in the direction of the most

143
00:13:26,029 --> 00:13:27,691
recent high or low.

144
00:13:27,691 --> 00:13:36,471
A new high or low is a signal that the current
momentum is to the upside or downside, by

145
00:13:36,471 --> 00:13:43,850
trading against this momentum you are unnecessarily
putting yourself at risk of losing money because

146
00:13:43,850 --> 00:13:47,110
you’re trying to trade against the trend.

147
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:56,210
Big Round Number Prices
I said it quite a few times before, one of

148
00:13:56,210 --> 00:14:02,300
the best places you can find high probability
support and resistance levels, is around the

149
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:05,860
big round number levels.

150
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:11,800
The support and resistance levels you can
find situated around these prices have a high

151
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:17,480
probability of causing a large reversal to
occur.

152
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:23,389
Just open any chart and you’ll see that
many big reversals will begin once the price

153
00:14:23,389 --> 00:14:33,850
has either almost hit a big round number,
or has just moved beyond it.

